data.text:
Dibrugarh, Assam, India

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 27.472834, 94.911964.

A wonderful city of Dibrugarh is located in northeastern Assam, right near the shores of the Brahmaputra river. With the population approaching to 190,000 people, the city is one of the most populated in the state. Dibrugarh is a key communication and industrial center of the region, with a few large agricultural and natural resource processing companies. However, it is famous as the Tea Capital of India since there is a great number of tea plantations surrounding the city. Tourism also contributes greatly in the city's economy.
